  "doc_id": "21415",
  "text": "At our institution we use the Spigelberg intraparenchymal bolt (GmbH & Co. KG) for ICP monitoring. This is favoured primarily because of its zero drift during prolonged monitoring and because the pulse amplitude can be analysed from the results. Some other bolts are known to drift [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] resulting in progressive inaccurate readings. Therefore prolonged monitoring can experience inaccurate readings over time depending on the bolt being used [CITATION_3] .",
